  h1 What is katakana?
  p Katakana is one of the two Japanese syllabic writing systems. Each of these systems provides a full list of sounds in the Japanese langugae. It consists of 46 characters and 25 diacritics. 
  p Katakana is most commonly used to write foreign words and names of countries. 
  p Click the button below to see a full list of katakana characters and their diacritics.
  a.go_next(href='katakana/list') List

